User visits malicious/compromised site
  │
  ├─ Site renders visually legitimate page (blog, corporate site, etc.)
  │
  ├─ Cookie consent overlay displayed
  │
  └─ User clicks Accept OR Decline
        │
        ├─ [Trigger 1] exhaustGPU() called
        │    WebGL shader saturates GPU → screen freezes
        │    Visual noise rendered to sell "something crashed"
        │
        ├─ [Trigger 2] requestFullscreen() called
        │    Browser attempts to show "Press Esc to exit" banner
        │    Banner suppressed by GPU freeze — user never sees it
        │
        ├─ GPU released → screen unfreezes
        │    Victim now sees full-screen fake Windows login
        │    (Or: fake BSOD → fake reboot → BitLocker PIN prompt)
        │
        ├─ [Trigger 3] navigator.keyboard.lock() called
        │    Alt+Tab, Win key, Esc all trapped
        │    User has no visible way to exit
        │
        ├─ Google One Tap iframes embedded and CSS-positioned
        │    Victim's own profile picture + username visible
        │    (Matches Windows account if Google = work account)
        │
        └─ Victim enters Windows password
              │
              └─ Credential sent to attacker C2 via fetch/XHR
